# iSeg HV Controller

A simple web-based controller for iSeg NHQ high voltage power supplies using Python, Streamlit, and RS-232 communication.

# Features

* 4-channel HV control
* Set voltage for each channel
* Adjustable ramp speed
* Apply all settings at once
* Shutdown all channels safely
* Live voltage and current readout
* Simple web UI via Streamlit

# Installation

```
git clone git@github.com:niikura-muon/iseg_hv.git
cd iseg_hv
python3 -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

# Usage

Run the Streamlit app:
 
```
streamlit run iseg_web.py
```

Then open the local web interface in your browser.

# Notes

Serial ports are currently configured as:

* /dev/ttyUSB0
* /dev/ttyUSB1

You may need to modify these depending on your hardware setup.

Make sure your user belongs to the dialout group:

sudo usermod -aG dialout $USER

# Disclaimer

This software controls high-voltage hardware.

Use at your own risk. Always verify output settings and follow proper laboratory safety procedures.